               <msContents>
                  <summary>A collection, mostly of poems, by various sixteenth-century Salonikan
                     Jewish authors, especially <persName>Saʿadiah Longo</persName></summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <title xml:lang="he" key="work_19">שירים</title>
                     <title xml:lang="jrb-Latn-x-lc" key="work_19">Shirim</title>
                     <author key="person_7059">
                        <persName>Longo, Saʿadiah ben Abraham, 1520-1600?</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="he">סעדיה בן אברהם לונגו</persName>
                     </author>
                     <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                     <note>This collection consists mainly of poems but also includes numerous
                        correspondences and short prose works. A significant portion of these are by
                        <persName key="person_7059">Saʻadiah Longo</persName>; the others appear to be the works of other Jewish authors
                        living in Salonika during the same period.</note>
                     <note>At the beginning and end of the manuscript (<locus>ff. i-vii,
                           233-238</locus>), additional poems have been copied by later hands; many
                        of these are duplicates of poems already found in the main part of the
                        manuscript.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
